#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np29"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:0.4"
msgid "Pattavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:0.5"
msgid "29. Sāsaṅkasikkhāpada"
msgstr "29. The training rule on what is risky"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-np29.1.1, pts-vp-en2.156, ms1V_2400
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū vutthavassā āraññakesu senāsanesu viharanti."
msgstr "At that time monks who had completed the rains residence were staying in wilderness dwellings."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.1.3"
msgid "Kattikacorakā bhikkhū—"
msgstr "Thieves who were active during the month of Kattika attacked the monks, thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.1.4"
msgid "“laddhalābhā”ti paripātenti."
msgstr "“They have obtained things.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.1.5"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The monks told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.1.6"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.1.7"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āraññakesu senāsanesu viharantena tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ antaraghare nikkhipitun”ti."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow monks who are staying in wilderness dwellings to store one of their three robes in an inhabited area.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-vp-pli3.263, pts-cs-bu-np29.1.2, ms1V_2401
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū—“bhagavatā anuññātaṃ āraññakesu senāsanesu viharantena tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ antaraghare nikkhipitun”ti tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ antaraghare nikkhipitvā atirekachārattaṃ vippavasanti."
msgstr "Knowing that the Master had made this allowance, monks stored one of their three robes in inhabited areas, and they stayed apart from them for more than six days."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.2"
msgid "Tāni cīvarāni nassantipi vinassantipi ḍayhantipi undūrehipi khajjanti."
msgstr "The robes were lost, destroyed, burnt, and eaten by rats."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū duccoḷā honti lūkhacīvarā."
msgstr "As a consequence those monks became poorly dressed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.4"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Other monks asked them"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.5"
msgid "“kissa tumhe, āvuso, duccoḷā lūkhacīvarā”ti?"
msgstr "why,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.6"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "and they told them what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.7"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.8"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.9"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ antaraghare nikkhipitvā atirekachārattaṃ vippavasissantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can those monks store one of their three robes in an inhabited area and then stay apart from it for more than six days?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms1V_2402
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.10"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū te anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.157
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.11"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ antaraghare nikkhipitvā atirekachārattaṃ vippavasantī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that some monks do this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.12"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.13"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.14"
msgid "kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ antaraghare nikkhipitvā atirekachārattaṃ vippavasissanti."
msgstr "Monks, how can those foolish men store one of their three robes in an inhabited area and then stay apart from it for more than six days?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.15"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.16"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc4, ms1V_2403
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.17"
msgid "“Upavassaṃ kho pana kattikapuṇṇamaṃ yāni kho pana tāni āraññakāni senāsanāni sāsaṅkasammatāni sappaṭibhayāni tathārūpesu bhikkhu senāsanesu viharanto ākaṅkhamāno tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ antaraghare nikkhipeyya, siyā ca tassa bhikkhuno kocideva paccayo tena cīvarena vippavāsāya."
msgstr "‘There are wilderness dwellings that are considered risky and dangerous. After observing the Kattika full moon that ends the rainy season, a monk who is staying in such a dwelling may store one of his three robes in an inhabited area, if he so desires, so long as he has a reason for staying apart from that robe."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.18"
msgid "Chārattaparamaṃ tena bhikkhunā tena cīvarena vippavasitabbaṃ."
msgstr "He should stay apart from that robe for six days at the most."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:1.2.19"
msgid "Tato ce uttari vippavaseyya, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "If he stays apart from it beyond that, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, pts-cs-bu-np29.2, ms1V_2404
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.1"
msgid "Upavassaṃ kho panāti"
msgstr "After observing:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.2"
msgid "vuṭṭhavassānaṃ."
msgstr "after completing the rainy season."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms1V_2405
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.3"
msgid "Kattikapuṇṇamanti"
msgstr "The Kattika full moon that ends the rainy season:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.4"
msgid "kattikacātumāsinī vuccati."
msgstr "the fourth full moon of the rainy season in the month of Kattika is what is meant."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_2406
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.5"
msgid "Yāni kho pana tāni āraññakāni senāsanānīti"
msgstr "There are wilderness dwellings:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.6"
msgid "āraññakaṃ nāma"
msgstr "it is called a wilderness dwelling"

# NOTE: The text reads “five hundred bow-lengths,” _pañcadhanusatikaṃ_. According to [](Sp-ṭ.2.92): “A measure of nine hand-spans of an ordinary hand, or a measure of four fore-arms when the bowstring is attached, this is called the teacher’s bow length,” _ācariyadhanu nāma pakatihatthena navavidatthippamāṇaṃ, jiyāya pana āropitāya catuhatthappamāṇa_. The teacher’s bow-length is the standard measure for bow-lengths, see [](Sp. 2.301.15). Given the estimate of 50 cm for one forearm (a _hattha_, sometimes translated as “cubit”) in BMC I, pp. 565-566, five hundred bow-lengths add up to about one kilometer.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.7"
msgid "senāsanaṃ pañcadhanusatikaṃ pacchimaṃ."
msgstr "if it is at least one kilometer away from any inhabited area."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, pts-vp-en2.158, ms1V_2407
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.8"
msgid "Sāsaṅkaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Risky:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.9"
msgid "ārāme ārāmūpacāre corānaṃ niviṭṭhokāso dissati, bhuttokāso dissati, ṭhitokāso dissati, nisinnokāso dissati, nipannokāso dissati."
msgstr "in the monastery, or in the vicinity of the monastery, thieves have been seen camping, eating, standing, seated, or lying down."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms1V_2408
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.10"
msgid "Sappaṭibhayaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Dangerous:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.11"
msgid "ārāme ārāmūpacāre corehi manussā hatā dissanti, viluttā dissanti, ākoṭitā dissanti."
msgstr "in the monastery, or in the vicinity of the monastery, thieves have been seen injuring, robbing, or beating people."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_2409
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.12"
msgid "Tathārūpesu bhikkhu senāsanesu viharantoti"
msgstr "A monk who is staying in such a dwelling:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.13"
msgid "evarūpesu bhikkhu senāsanesu viharanto."
msgstr "a monk who is staying in that kind of dwelling."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, pts-vp-pli3.264, ms1V_2410
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.14"
msgid "Ākaṅkhamānoti"
msgstr "If he so desires:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.15"
msgid "icchamāno."
msgstr "if he so wishes."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_2411
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.16"
msgid "Tiṇṇaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaranti"
msgstr "One of his three robes:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.17"
msgid "saṅghāṭiṃ vā uttarāsaṅgaṃ vā antaravāsakaṃ vā."
msgstr "the outer robe, the upper robe, or the lower robe."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_2412
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.18"
msgid "Antaraghare nikkhipeyyāti"
msgstr "May store […] in an inhabited area:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.19"
msgid "samantā gocaragāme nikkhipeyya."
msgstr "may store it anywhere in his alms village."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_2413
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.20"
msgid "Siyā ca tassa bhikkhuno kocideva paccayo tena cīvarena vippavāsāyāti"
msgstr "So long as he has a reason for staying apart from that robe:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.21"
msgid "siyā paccayo siyā karaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "if there is a reason, if there is something to be done."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc15, ms1V_2414
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.22"
msgid "Chārattaparamaṃ tena bhikkhunā tena cīvarena vippavasitabbanti"
msgstr "He should stay apart from that robe for six days at the most:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.23"
msgid "chārattaparamatā vippavasitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he should stay apart from it for six days at the maximum."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc16, ms1V_2415
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.24"
msgid "Aññatra bhikkhusammutiyāti"
msgstr "Except if the monks have agreed:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.25"
msgid "ṭhapetvā bhikkhusammutiṃ."
msgstr "unless he has the permission of the monks."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc17, ms1V_2416
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.26"
msgid "Tato ce uttari vippavaseyyāti"
msgstr "If he stays apart from it beyond that:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.27"
msgid "sattame aruṇuggamane nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "the robe becomes subject to relinquishment at dawn on the seventh day."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.28"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.29"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. HTML: <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.30"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in [Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17](pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13), with appropriate substitutions. "

#. HTML: </span> 
#. VAR: vippavutthaṃ → vippavuṭṭhaṃ (c1, c2)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.31"
msgid "idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ atirekachārattaṃ vippavutthaṃ, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this robe which I have stayed apart from for more than six days without the permission of the monks is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.32"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmīti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.33"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.34"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.35"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.35a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc18, ms1V_2417, pts-vp-en2.159
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.36"
msgid "Atirekachāratte atirekasaññī vippavasati, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than six days and he perceives it as more and he is staying apart from it, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.37"
msgid "Atirekachāratte vematiko vippavasati, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than six days, but he is unsure if it is, and he is staying apart from it, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.38"
msgid "Atirekachāratte ūnakasaññī vippavasati, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than six days, but he does not perceives it as more, and he is staying apart from it, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.39"
msgid "Appaccuddhaṭe paccuddhaṭasaññī … pe …"
msgstr "If the determination has not been given up, but he perceives it as given up …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.40"
msgid "avissajjite vissajjitasaññī …"
msgstr "If the robe has not been given away, but he perceives it as given away …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.41"
msgid "anaṭṭhe naṭṭhasaññī …"
msgstr "If the robe has not been lost, but he perceives it as lost …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.42"
msgid "avinaṭṭhe vinaṭṭhasaññī …"
msgstr "If the robe has not been destroyed, but he perceives it as destroyed …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.43"
msgid "adaḍḍhe daḍḍhasaññī …"
msgstr "If the robe has not been burnt, but he perceives it as burnt …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.44"
msgid "avilutte viluttasaññī vippavasati, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If the robe has not been stolen, but he perceives it as stolen, and he is staying apart from it, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc19, ms1V_2418
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.45"
msgid "Nissaggiyaṃ cīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he uses a robe that should be relinquished without first relinquishing it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.46"
msgid "Ūnakachāratte atirekasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than six days, but he perceives it as more, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.47"
msgid "Ūnakachāratte vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than six days, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.48"
msgid "Ūnakachāratte ūnakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is less than six days and he perceives it as less, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.48a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc20, ms1V_2419
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.49"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.50"
msgid "chārattaṃ vippavasati,"
msgstr "if he stays apart from the robe for six days;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.51"
msgid "ūnakachārattaṃ vippavasati,"
msgstr "if he stays apart from the robe for less than six days;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.52"
msgid "chārattaṃ vippavasitvā puna gāmasīmaṃ okkamitvā vasitvā pakkamati,"
msgstr "if, after staying apart from it for six days, he stays overnight within the village boundary and then departs;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.53"
msgid "antochārattaṃ paccuddharati, vissajjeti, nassati, vinassati, ḍayhati, acchinditvā gaṇhanti, vissāsaṃ gaṇhanti,"
msgstr "if within the six days he gives up the determination, or the robe is given away, lost, destroyed, burnt, stolen, or taken on trust;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.54"
msgid "bhikkhusammutiyā,"
msgstr "if he has the permission of the monks;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.55"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np29:2.56"
